data.title: Blue Suede Shoes by Harry Fontana and The Tennessee Tone Boys
meta_keywords: Harry Fontana and The Tennessee Tone Boys
data.meta_description: Blue Suede Shoes by Harry Fontana and The Tennessee Tone Boys was written by Carl Perkins [US1] and was first recorded and released by Carl Perkins [US1] in 1955. Harry Fontana and The Tennessee Tone Boys released it on the album American-Finnish Rock 'a' Billy in 2011. It was covered by The Rock Band Revival, Slasher, Ben Cash, Mack Allen Smith and other artists.
